  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empower local communities to protect dry forests</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With only 5% remaining, dry forests are one of the most endangered ecosystems in the world. Native trees are heavily logged, yet crucial to the survival and wellbeing of local communities and wildlife. Located on Peru&apos;s arid northern coast, this project will work with low-income farmers and diverse community members to reforest this threatened habitat. Local people will be trained on how to protect and sustainably manage the dry forests in ways that boost their income and the local economy.</narrative>
  </description>
